1
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,640
Between us, it'll never end because of me.

2
00:02:43,720 --> 00:02:44,880
It'll be you.

3
00:02:45,480 --> 00:02:47,120
<i>If I were just a little higher,</i>

4
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:49,000
<i>maybe I wouldn't have to envy Trai.</i>

5
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:51,680
But you made promises
without consulting the board.

6
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:53,040
If we can't deliver,

7
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:54,560
it'll become an even bigger disaster.

8
00:02:54,640 --> 00:02:56,680
Then we deliver.
What's so hard about that?

9
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:59,280
Why the hell can't brothers work together?

10
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:01,880
Or you want to be chairman instead of me?

11
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:04,760
Trai is making my plan harder.

12
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:06,240
- Hey!
- Go get him!

13
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:07,240
Go!

14
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:08,960
- Tritot!
- Come out!

15
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:11,080
- Don't come closer.
- Dad.

16
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:13,520
I'm sorry, my son. I'm sorry that

17
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:16,680
I couldn't be a good father sooner.

18
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:21,080
<i>For our family, I'll try again.</i>

19
00:03:21,160 --> 00:03:24,200
Are you really going to let
your brother run Be Rich?

20
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:27,200
Now there's only one person left,
the chairman.

21
00:03:31,720 --> 00:03:34,200
From when Mr. Tritot arrived home
until when the ambulance came,

22
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:35,640
no one went in or out of the house.

23
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:36,640
And the cameras inside?

24
00:03:36,720 --> 00:03:39,440
There aren't any.
Mr. Tritot valued his privacy very highly.

25
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:41,440
If someone really pushed Dad,

26
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:43,880
they must have known
where the cameras were.

27
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:46,200
So you think
it was someone inside the house?

28
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:48,880
Mr. Rachen, you can't come in.

29
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,040
You don't want me to visit Dad?

30
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:54,240
Yes. For safety reasons.

31
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:55,720
Safety?

32
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:59,240
- Mr. Trai!
- What kind of bullshit safety is that?!

33
00:03:59,320 --> 00:04:00,800
Safe from you, you bastard!

34
00:04:00,880 --> 00:04:02,840
Don't think I don't know
what you did to Dad.

35
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:03,920
What did I do?!

36
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,400
Say it! What did I do?!

37
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:07,400
You pushed Dad down the stairs.

38
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:09,920
Me? I pushed Dad down the stairs?

39
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:16,320
Yeah. You want Be Rich
so badly, don't you?

40
00:04:16,399 --> 00:04:18,440
If Dad's gone, you get everything.

41
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:21,320
What the hell are you thinking? Huh?

42
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:24,440
If Dad's gone,
Be Rich means nothing to me.

43
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:26,600
What would I even take Be Rich for?!

44
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:29,080
For yourself.

45
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:31,520
You're not Dad's real son.
You're just the mistress's kid.

46
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:33,680
You only love Dad's money, you bastard!

47
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:41,440
Don't you dare look down on my love.

48
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:43,640
You've never known anything.

49
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:46,760
You know what? Even as Dad's real son,

50
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:48,840
you can't compare to me at all.

51
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:56,200
Then answer me this. Where were you?
Why did you let Dad fall down the stairs?

52
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:58,960
And where the hell were you?!

53
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:00,160
I asked you first!

54
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:02,440
You never stayed to take care of Dad.

55
00:05:02,520 --> 00:05:05,760
All you ever do is create problems
then run away from them.

56
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:09,440
You take the credit for yourself
and dump the blame on others.

57
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:12,400
You've never even opened your eyes
to see what was really happening!

58
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:14,720
Dad ended up like this because of you.

59
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:16,240
He fell down the stairs because of you!

60
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:19,200
Are you crazy? That's not true!

61
00:05:19,280 --> 00:05:21,000
You don't know anything at all.

62
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:24,120
You and Darin's case

63
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:27,240
made Dad collapse and go
to the hospital so many times.

64
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:30,720
Dad got heart disease
because he was stressed about you.

65
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:32,440
He needed surgery,

66
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:34,880
needed to see doctors every month.

67
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:38,000
And who took him?
Who took care of him? Me!

68
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:41,760
I loved Dad and worried about him
more than his real son ever did.

69
00:05:41,840 --> 00:05:43,520
And you still have the nerve

70
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:45,920
to think it was me?
You thought I hurt your dad?!

71
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:51,360
You nearly killed him
countless times already,

72
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:53,800
and why the hell
do you only care about him now?!

73
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:56,000
Huh?!

74
00:05:57,480 --> 00:06:00,320
You know what? Dad taught me

75
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:02,120
to love you,

76
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:05,920
to see you as my real younger brother.

77
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:08,560
And you?

78
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:10,880
Have you ever seen me as your brother?

79
00:06:10,960 --> 00:06:14,000
Have you ever seen me as family?!

80
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:58,120
Mr. Rachen.

81
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:24,200
Are you okay, Mr. Rachen?

82
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:30,920
Then you need to go
to the company immediately.

83
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:32,520
Here.

84
00:07:37,520 --> 00:07:40,400
MR. TRITOT BOWORNMONGKOLPHONG,
BE RICH'S CHAIRMAN, IS SEVERELY ILL

85
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:01,760
I don't know
who caused Dad to fall down the stairs.

86
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:07,320
But Dad being sick
really is because of me.

87
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,360
Your dad

88
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:14,640
might've already been unwell before that.

89
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:17,280
I checked.

90
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:21,880
Dad's symptoms started
when I had that car accident.

91
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:26,000
I never knew how stressed
he was because of me.

92
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:28,800
Rachen was right.

93
00:08:28,880 --> 00:08:31,200
I only cared about myself.

94
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:35,080
I kept blaming Dad for hurting me.

95
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:37,039
But in the end, it was me

96
00:08:37,919 --> 00:08:40,000
who kept hurting him all along.

97
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,200
Mr. Trai.

98
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:45,440
I kept saying "I'll change tomorrow."

99
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:49,680
But tomorrow might not even exist anymore.

100
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:52,280
Mr. Trai…

101
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:56,440
I thought Dad was strong,

102
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,400
that he'd stay and scold me,

103
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:01,520
argue with me forever.

104
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:04,760
But he could leave me at any time.

105
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:07,640
Today, I still have a dad.

106
00:09:08,560 --> 00:09:10,440
Tomorrow, I might not.

107
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:18,520
I'm scared…

108
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:21,120
I'm scared Dad will leave me,

109
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:24,600
just like Mom did.

110
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:37,680
Your dad is very strong, you know.

111
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:40,400
That's why you never knew he was sick.

112
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,920
He'll get better.

113
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:46,160
Your dad won't leave you, Mr. Trai.

114
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:49,840
I really want to start over with him.

115
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:53,160
I want us
to still have a tomorrow together.

116
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:57,240
I want to eat Dad's fried chicken.

117
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:00,720
I really want to hug him one more time.

118
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:47,880
The company's situation
is already unstable.

119
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:51,640
Be Rich can't afford to have
the top leadership position vacant now.

120
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:55,560
Mr. Tritot might not be seriously ill.
We shouldn't jump to conclusions.

121
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:57,720
But shouldn't we prepare
for every possibility?

122
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:59,600
We still have Rachen.

123
00:10:59,680 --> 00:11:00,960
But don't forget.

124
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:03,160
Mr. Trai Bowornmongkolphong

125
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:05,200
holds the second-largest share
after Mr. Tritot.

126
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:09,760
And he's trying to change Be Rich
with his absurd ideals.

127
00:11:10,680 --> 00:11:12,240
I don't want anyone to be careless.

128
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:14,800
What if he takes this opportunity

129
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:16,880
to fully take control of Be Rich?

130
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:24,480
I think we should propose names and vote.

131
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:27,240
We need to appoint
an acting chairman as soon as possible.

132
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:36,880
That won't be necessary.

133
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:38,800
My father isn't seriously ill.
He'll be fine.

134
00:11:39,520 --> 00:11:41,760
No need to appoint anyone
to replace him right now.

135
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:55,600
The chairman
being hospitalized is a big deal.

136
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:59,480
If outsiders find out,
it could affect the company's stability.

137
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:01,960
- You understand?
- Then don't let outsiders find out.

138
00:12:04,040 --> 00:12:08,320
Mr. Rachen, I see you
as a young man with a bright future.

139
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:10,600
But if you never plan ahead

140
00:12:10,680 --> 00:12:12,920
or never seize the opportunities
that come your way,

141
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,960
then you'll just stay stuck where you are.

142
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:16,720
You'll never move forward.

143
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:20,080
I understand what you want,
Mrs. Mookmanee.

144
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:21,680
But Dad is just a little unwell.

145
00:12:21,760 --> 00:12:24,120
He'll rest for a few days and get better.

146
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:26,520
Thank you very much for your concern.

147
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:45,640
He's trying to defy me.

148
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:47,360
Mr. Rachen?

149
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:52,720
But I think he looks like he's
totally intimidated by you, right?

150
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:56,760
He humiliated me in the meeting.
And he spoke to me in that cold tone.

151
00:12:56,840 --> 00:12:58,800
He doesn't want me
going anywhere near his father.

152
00:12:59,920 --> 00:13:02,080
I'm sure he's hiding something.

153
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:08,480
Or could it be that Tritot
isn't really sick the way he's claiming?

154
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:18,640
Mr. Trai.

155
00:13:19,960 --> 00:13:20,920
Are you okay?

156
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,680
If Dad didn't fall by himself…

157
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:38,120
then who did it?

158
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:40,480
And why?

159
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:48,760
Dad got home at 11 p.m.

160
00:13:50,080 --> 00:13:51,800
The maid found him at almost 1 a.m.

161
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:54,040
Between those times, what was he doing?

162
00:13:57,160 --> 00:13:58,560
Did anyone come into this room?

163
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:02,800
Not yet. The maid hadn't come in
to clean either. I checked.

164
00:14:04,840 --> 00:14:06,360
So Dad didn't go to sleep?

165
00:14:12,040 --> 00:14:13,280
Mr. Trai.

166
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:18,960
Do you know the password?

167
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:21,400
Probably his birthday.

168
00:14:24,080 --> 00:14:25,000
It wasn't locked.

169
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,000
Why is there nothing on here?

170
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:41,360
I don't know what's wrong.
It's like it got a virus.

171
00:14:44,440 --> 00:14:45,760
Then get the phone and the laptop checked.

172
00:14:46,520 --> 00:14:47,360
Yes, sir.

173
00:14:48,880 --> 00:14:49,960
Where were you last night?

174
00:14:54,920 --> 00:14:56,440
I asked you. Where were you last night?

175
00:14:58,200 --> 00:15:00,360
You're getting more and more
like your father every day.

176
00:15:01,040 --> 00:15:03,320
Jealous, possessive. What?
You want to be my husband too?

177
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:06,560
Dad is in the hospital.

178
00:15:10,760 --> 00:15:12,840
His heart condition's acting up again?

179
00:15:12,920 --> 00:15:14,560
So how many days this time?

180
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:16,000
I'll pack accordingly.

181
00:15:17,040 --> 00:15:18,400
You really don't feel anything?

182
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:21,120
You hurt Dad, didn't you?

183
00:15:22,120 --> 00:15:25,200
Are you insane? Your dad was
already sick. How is that my problem?

184
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:26,960
I've seen him
swallowing handfuls of pills,

185
00:15:27,040 --> 00:15:29,120
heart disease, high blood pressure.

186
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:30,600
And look at how he lives.

187
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:35,440
Hey, if your dad dies, he deserves it.

188
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:38,800
Hey!

189
00:15:38,880 --> 00:15:40,240
Can you stop using violence?

190
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:41,880
Didn't you hear what your ex just said?

191
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:43,320
I did.

192
00:15:48,320 --> 00:15:49,360
I was angry.

193
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:52,360
He suddenly came at me
looking for a fight.

194
00:15:52,440 --> 00:15:54,680
- I just wanted to mess with him.
- Liar!

195
00:15:56,320 --> 00:15:57,920
Where were you last night?

196
00:15:58,520 --> 00:16:00,280
I slept over at my mom's.

197
00:16:00,880 --> 00:16:02,400
What happened, Trai?

198
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:05,360
Dad fell down the stairs.
He's at the hospital.

199
00:16:06,440 --> 00:16:07,360
Huh?

200
00:16:08,840 --> 00:16:12,120
Then how is he?

201
00:16:12,920 --> 00:16:13,800
He's not dead yet.

202
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:17,160
Don't forget your ex is an actress.

203
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:19,560
I'm not acting.

204
00:16:22,040 --> 00:16:25,760
Trai, I really don't know anything.

205
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:28,240
I slept at my mom's.

206
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:30,120
I didn't even see Mr. Tritot.

207
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:32,480
When I left, he still wasn't home.

208
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:34,760
But you just fought with him
the other day, didn't you?

209
00:16:35,920 --> 00:16:38,320
You broke things all over the house,
so loudly that the maids freaked out.

210
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:41,240
So what? You fought
with Mr. Tritot too, didn't you?

211
00:16:42,520 --> 00:16:44,640
People are saying
you want to steal his position.

212
00:16:44,720 --> 00:16:47,200
Shut up. You never even go
to the office. What would you know?

213
00:16:47,280 --> 00:16:48,600
I heard it, okay?

214
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:51,320
You weren't happy that Mr. Tritot
let Trai into the office,

215
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:54,560
so you threw a tantrum and made him
choose between you and Trai.

216
00:16:55,880 --> 00:16:58,920
You thought he'd choose you, right?

217
00:16:59,680 --> 00:17:00,600
Sorry.

218
00:17:01,360 --> 00:17:03,520
He'll always choose his real son.

219
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:05,560
Why would he choose
the mistress's kid like you?

220
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:10,200
Why? Because I'm not his real son,

221
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:11,760
that makes me the villain?

222
00:17:11,839 --> 00:17:14,160
And a rebellious son like you

223
00:17:14,240 --> 00:17:16,319
and that woman
who'd do anything for money,

224
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:18,640
aren't you both also the suspicious ones?

225
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:32,720
Here. Get this washed too.

226
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:42,800
Weird.

227
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:44,560
So weird.

228
00:17:45,560 --> 00:17:46,400
Weird how?

229
00:17:46,480 --> 00:17:49,240
Mr. Tritot fell down the stairs
and had a brain hemorrhage.

230
00:17:49,320 --> 00:17:53,080
The surgery is done. The doctor's
monitoring him now. What's weird?

231
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:57,080
What's weird isn't Mr. Tritot.

232
00:17:57,920 --> 00:17:59,680
What's weird is you.

233
00:18:00,480 --> 00:18:02,440
Trai already went back,

234
00:18:02,520 --> 00:18:04,760
so why are you still staying
to watch his dad?

235
00:18:05,440 --> 00:18:07,880
And you even called me
to ask about his condition.

236
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:09,360
Very weird.

237
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:11,560
Because Mr. Trai went back.

238
00:18:11,640 --> 00:18:13,160
So I'm staying instead.

239
00:18:13,240 --> 00:18:16,320
You're in med school, aren't you?
So you should be able to tell me.

240
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:18,400
Will Mr. Tritot recover?

241
00:18:18,480 --> 00:18:20,480
What's going to happen?
Will he get better?

242
00:18:20,560 --> 00:18:22,640
What do we have to do? How can we help?

243
00:18:24,040 --> 00:18:25,320
Be honest.

244
00:18:26,360 --> 00:18:28,440
Are you getting paid for this or what?

245
00:18:28,520 --> 00:18:31,080
This is life or death, Kanah.

246
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:33,040
Why are you talking about compensation?

247
00:18:33,120 --> 00:18:34,200
There.

248
00:18:35,560 --> 00:18:37,600
You're letting your heart lead now.

249
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:39,920
It's obviously love.

250
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:43,400
- Kanah.
- Ow!

251
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:44,800
Ow! That hurts, Bung!

252
00:18:44,880 --> 00:18:47,680
His dad is in a coma,

253
00:18:47,760 --> 00:18:49,280
and you're still talking nonsense.

254
00:18:49,360 --> 00:18:51,280
I'm just teasing.

255
00:18:51,360 --> 00:18:53,600
I paid to send you to med school.

256
00:18:53,680 --> 00:18:55,440
If you can't answer something this basic,

257
00:18:56,280 --> 00:18:58,600
- give me my coffee back.
- Hey, careful, it'll spill!

258
00:18:58,680 --> 00:19:02,320
Jeez, I tease you a little,
and you get all shy and run away!

259
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:05,760
Wait for me. Wait.

260
00:19:08,320 --> 00:19:10,480
Bung, Bung, whoa.

261
00:19:10,560 --> 00:19:13,840
If you want to help,
you can help by giving support.

262
00:19:15,520 --> 00:19:17,160
I know that.

263
00:19:17,240 --> 00:19:20,320
Tell me something that's
actually worth your 25,000-baht tuition.

264
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:21,440
Alright.

265
00:19:21,520 --> 00:19:23,360
And you'll have to actually do it, okay?

266
00:19:23,440 --> 00:19:25,200
Patients need support.

267
00:19:25,280 --> 00:19:27,440
And the patient's family
needs it even more.

268
00:19:27,520 --> 00:19:30,880
Taking care of someone sick
is so draining, you know?

269
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:32,960
You can't just show up
and say, "Hang in there!"

270
00:19:33,040 --> 00:19:35,200
That's not enough.

271
00:19:35,280 --> 00:19:38,160
You have to stay by his side,
stay close to him,

272
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:41,480
so whenever Trai turns around,
he sees you.

273
00:19:41,560 --> 00:19:44,320
And hold his hand if you can.

274
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:47,120
And if you can hug him, like this,

275
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:49,840
then hug him tight. Like this.

276
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:52,600
- Yeah. I already hugged him.
- Huh?

277
00:19:54,680 --> 00:19:55,520
What?

278
00:19:56,280 --> 00:19:58,840
You mean

279
00:19:58,920 --> 00:20:00,720
you know you should hug? Or…

280
00:20:00,800 --> 00:20:02,440
- you actually hugged Trai?
- Mr. Tritot?

281
00:20:02,520 --> 00:20:04,720
The family isn't allowing visitors
under any circumstances.

282
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:07,240
Bung, why didn't you tell me?

283
00:20:07,320 --> 00:20:09,880
- Even Trai wouldn't tell me anything.
- Really?

284
00:20:10,480 --> 00:20:12,200
So? Bung.

285
00:20:12,280 --> 00:20:13,840
How far have you and Trai gone now?

286
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:18,040
Just hugging, or…

287
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:25,240
Ow! It's hot. Bung!

288
00:20:25,320 --> 00:20:26,360
Whoa.

289
00:20:29,280 --> 00:20:31,960
Go back and focus on your studies.

290
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:34,160
Make it worth
all my hard work and your tuition.

291
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:36,920
- Go. Go, go, go!
- Ow, ow, ow! Okay. I'm going.

292
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:49,280
This confirms Ms. Darin's whereabouts.

293
00:20:49,360 --> 00:20:51,040
She left around a little past 9 p.m.

294
00:20:51,120 --> 00:20:53,400
The driver confirms
she went to her mother's.

295
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:56,160
According to the camera,
she didn't go anywhere all night.

296
00:20:58,280 --> 00:20:59,120
What about Rachen?

297
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:02,040
Here.

298
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:05,320
From 10 p.m. to 2 a.m.,

299
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:08,480
Mr. Rachen was drinking alone.
Then he had the driver pick him up.

300
00:21:09,120 --> 00:21:10,920
So for the time it happened,

301
00:21:11,840 --> 00:21:13,920
Rachen has a solid alibi.

302
00:21:22,280 --> 00:21:24,520
Wait. Who's this?

303
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:28,400
Rut, Mr. Rachen's subordinate.

304
00:21:28,480 --> 00:21:29,720
You've probably met him before.

305
00:21:30,320 --> 00:21:31,240
Rut?

306
00:21:32,760 --> 00:21:33,920
Where have I seen him?

307
00:21:42,240 --> 00:21:43,480
Or is it…

308
00:21:47,040 --> 00:21:47,880
Wait.

309
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:52,520
What do you want now?

310
00:21:55,520 --> 00:21:56,760
We've met before, haven't we?

311
00:21:58,040 --> 00:22:00,360
Yes, sir. I work for Mr. Rachen.

312
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:02,040
We've met many times.

313
00:22:02,680 --> 00:22:03,760
What about at my mom's school?

314
00:22:19,120 --> 00:22:21,800
Hey. Are you suspecting my man?

315
00:22:21,880 --> 00:22:23,080
How long have you known him?

316
00:22:23,160 --> 00:22:24,720
Gosh, Trai.

317
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:27,160
Stop being crazy.
Stop blaming other people.

318
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:30,360
The person in this house
who hates Dad the most is your ex.

319
00:22:31,040 --> 00:22:34,000
Try using your brain instead of the thing
between your legs for once.

320
00:22:34,080 --> 00:22:36,360
Watch the person you should be watching.

321
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:38,480
Or you'll be next.

322
00:22:52,360 --> 00:22:53,360
No scar…

323
00:22:55,360 --> 00:22:56,920
If it's not him, then who is it?

324
00:23:00,920 --> 00:23:01,760
Excuse me.

325
00:23:07,080 --> 00:23:07,880
Pakbung?

326
00:23:10,280 --> 00:23:11,920
Are you sick?

327
00:23:12,560 --> 00:23:13,800
Did you get hurt?

328
00:23:14,680 --> 00:23:16,160
Or is it Kanah? What happened to him?

329
00:23:16,240 --> 00:23:18,280
Who are you visiting, sir?

330
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:20,360
Sir?

331
00:23:25,680 --> 00:23:28,800
I'm visiting a friend. My friend is sick.

332
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:30,240
A friend?

333
00:23:31,120 --> 00:23:33,200
Your friend is Mr. Tritot?

334
00:23:34,280 --> 00:23:35,960
I saw you asking the nurse.

335
00:23:36,880 --> 00:23:38,360
You know Mr. Tritot too?

336
00:23:40,400 --> 00:23:42,040
I work for him.

337
00:23:42,760 --> 00:23:45,840
I didn't know you knew Mr. Tritot too.

338
00:23:46,840 --> 00:23:50,120
Yeah. I know him. I know him well.

339
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:52,360
We've run into each other
at Be Rich a lot.

340
00:23:52,440 --> 00:23:55,000
Mrs. Mook, my boss,
is a partner of Mr. Tritot.

341
00:23:55,080 --> 00:23:57,720
Mrs. Mook told me to come visit.

342
00:23:57,800 --> 00:24:00,560
So, what room is Mr. Tritot in?

343
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:02,440
Take me there, Pakbung.

344
00:24:04,240 --> 00:24:05,600
Mr. Tritot has COVID.

345
00:24:05,680 --> 00:24:07,360
It's not severe,

346
00:24:07,440 --> 00:24:10,920
but the doctor wants him isolated.
They're worried he'll infect others,

347
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:12,240
so visits aren't allowed.

348
00:24:20,240 --> 00:24:22,160
Mrs. Mook, I got an update.

349
00:24:22,240 --> 00:24:24,080
I met someone close to Mr. Tritot.

350
00:24:24,160 --> 00:24:26,360
They said Mr. Tritot has COVID.

351
00:24:26,440 --> 00:24:27,920
No visitors allowed.

352
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:33,280
Alright, I'll head back now.

353
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:36,440
Yes.

354
00:24:42,720 --> 00:24:44,480
I knew it.
He's not here with good intentions.

355
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:50,720
But why does she want
to know about Mr. Tritot?

356
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:14,160
Are you trying to fool your own dad?

357
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:18,360
ICU?

358
00:25:18,440 --> 00:25:21,360
Yes. They're covering it up.

359
00:25:21,440 --> 00:25:23,160
No visitors are allowed.

360
00:25:23,240 --> 00:25:25,000
But luckily,

361
00:25:25,080 --> 00:25:27,320
I ran into someone close to Mr. Tritot.

362
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:30,760
Even if I don't know the full details,

363
00:25:30,840 --> 00:25:34,040
I can say for sure
he's definitely in a coma.

364
00:25:39,520 --> 00:25:40,560
Very good.

365
00:25:41,800 --> 00:25:43,400
It wasn't a waste to send you.

366
00:25:44,120 --> 00:25:46,280
I worked really hard

367
00:25:46,360 --> 00:25:47,600
for you, Mrs. Mookmanee.

368
00:25:58,360 --> 00:26:01,880
50,000. Enough for your hard work?

369
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:12,040
And if it's not enough…

370
00:26:14,280 --> 00:26:18,000
what reward will you give me extra?

371
00:26:47,480 --> 00:26:48,360
Hello, Pakbung.

372
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:50,520
You haven't gone home, right?

373
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:54,160
Okay. Then I'll go visit Dad first.
See you in a bit.

374
00:26:55,160 --> 00:26:56,080
Trai.

375
00:27:14,640 --> 00:27:16,160
How is Mr. Tritot?

376
00:27:16,240 --> 00:27:18,400
Not bad but not good either.

377
00:27:19,080 --> 00:27:20,760
Can I go in and see him?

378
00:27:22,440 --> 00:27:23,440
Not yet, Da.

379
00:27:24,920 --> 00:27:25,880
Dad needs to rest.

380
00:27:26,800 --> 00:27:28,760
Do you think the same as Mr. Rachen?

381
00:27:30,360 --> 00:27:32,320
Do you really think I hurt Mr. Tritot?

382
00:27:34,360 --> 00:27:35,840
What did you fight with Dad about?

383
00:27:36,800 --> 00:27:38,600
About me wanting to work.

384
00:27:38,680 --> 00:27:41,040
But Mr. Tritot wouldn't let me.

385
00:27:41,120 --> 00:27:42,880
So we argued.

386
00:27:42,960 --> 00:27:46,720
I admit I was furious,
so I ran off to sleep at my mom's.

387
00:27:47,560 --> 00:27:49,200
That's all it was, Trai.

388
00:27:49,280 --> 00:27:51,600
I didn't do anything to Mr. Tritot.

389
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:55,760
And when you found out
Dad fell down the stairs, were you happy?

390
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:58,920
Trai.
Why would you ask something like that?

391
00:27:59,520 --> 00:28:00,680
Do you love my dad?

392
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:06,240
Even if I didn't marry
Mr. Tritot for love,

393
00:28:06,320 --> 00:28:08,880
I still don't want
anything to happen to him.

394
00:28:09,800 --> 00:28:11,880
Because he's the father of the person I…

395
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:17,480
Because he's your father.

396
00:28:19,480 --> 00:28:20,840
If this were before now,

397
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,240
I'd probably believe you.

398
00:28:24,760 --> 00:28:25,960
That's not true.

399
00:28:26,800 --> 00:28:28,240
If it were before now…

400
00:28:31,920 --> 00:28:34,560
you wouldn't even suspect me at all.

401
00:28:35,560 --> 00:28:37,440
You'd be on my side.

402
00:28:37,520 --> 00:28:39,640
You'd believe in me.

403
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:45,760
I made one wrong choice one time,

404
00:28:45,840 --> 00:28:48,360
and that makes me wrong,

405
00:28:48,440 --> 00:28:51,680
makes me evil in your eyes
about everything. Is that it?

406
00:28:58,040 --> 00:29:01,440
If even you don't trust me,
then no one will.

407
00:29:01,520 --> 00:29:05,040
If I look cruel enough
to hurt your father,

408
00:29:05,120 --> 00:29:07,760
then take me to the police.

409
00:29:07,840 --> 00:29:09,920
Turn me in
if that's what will satisfy you.

410
00:29:32,520 --> 00:29:34,040
Why am I hiding?

411
00:29:44,160 --> 00:29:46,480
I believe you were
at your mom's last night.

412
00:29:46,560 --> 00:29:49,520
But today, Dad really does need rest.
You should go home first.

413
00:29:55,080 --> 00:29:56,240
Trai,

414
00:29:56,840 --> 00:29:58,400
I know you're hurting.

415
00:29:59,080 --> 00:30:00,480
You're confused.

416
00:30:00,560 --> 00:30:03,040
But I'm not the person
you need to suspect.

417
00:30:03,120 --> 00:30:05,400
I've never wished you harm,

418
00:30:05,480 --> 00:30:07,960
now or ever.

419
00:30:08,560 --> 00:30:10,320
I'm on your side.

420
00:30:15,920 --> 00:30:16,800
Excuse me.

421
00:30:18,400 --> 00:30:20,200
But by his side,

422
00:30:21,880 --> 00:30:23,400
he already has me.

423
00:30:39,640 --> 00:30:42,160
No, no, no. I can't fall in love.

424
00:30:42,240 --> 00:30:43,640
Love is pure loss.

425
00:30:43,720 --> 00:30:45,840
No love. No heart. Absolutely not.

426
00:30:47,360 --> 00:30:49,320
- Pakbung.
- The moment I use my heart, I'm screwed.

427
00:30:49,400 --> 00:30:51,360
Pakbung, didn't you say
you'd stay by my side?

428
00:30:54,720 --> 00:30:57,400
I'm right here. I'm not going anywhere.

429
00:30:58,160 --> 00:31:00,600
Then what's with you
speed-walking away from me?

430
00:31:00,680 --> 00:31:02,040
Are you jealous of me and Darin?

431
00:31:02,120 --> 00:31:05,040
Whoa, jealous of what? Who's jealous?

432
00:31:05,120 --> 00:31:06,840
Friends don't get jealous, okay?

433
00:31:07,960 --> 00:31:09,400
But you look…

434
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:13,680
I'm just annoyed.

435
00:31:13,760 --> 00:31:14,840
Annoyed about what?

436
00:31:14,920 --> 00:31:16,760
Just annoyed, okay?

437
00:31:16,840 --> 00:31:18,640
Have you not been annoyed by anyone?

438
00:31:18,720 --> 00:31:21,560
There's nothing between Da and me.

439
00:31:21,640 --> 00:31:23,920
I just wanted to see
if she's using me or not.

440
00:31:25,640 --> 00:31:28,400
You went so close to see.
Are you nearsighted?

441
00:31:28,480 --> 00:31:31,560
And you were wiping her tears,
holding her hands.

442
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:34,960
You know she's lying,
but you still let her fool you like that?

443
00:31:36,640 --> 00:31:38,040
All that, and you're not jealous?

444
00:31:38,720 --> 00:31:39,680
I'm not jealous.

445
00:31:39,760 --> 00:31:41,120
- Jealous.
- No.

446
00:31:41,200 --> 00:31:42,640
- Jealous.
- No.

447
00:31:42,720 --> 00:31:43,800
- Jealous.
- No.

448
00:31:43,880 --> 00:31:44,920
- Jealous.
- No!

449
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:47,600
- Jealous.
- Yeah, I'm jealous. What?

450
00:31:49,360 --> 00:31:51,920
Think what you want.

451
00:31:52,840 --> 00:31:53,800
I'm leaving.

452
00:32:01,080 --> 00:32:01,920
I'm…

453
00:32:03,360 --> 00:32:04,200
hungry.

454
00:32:13,520 --> 00:32:15,720
Travel fee, plus delivery fee.

455
00:32:15,800 --> 00:32:17,600
I'm adding 10% to it.

456
00:32:20,240 --> 00:32:22,800
I'll open it for you too.

457
00:32:24,280 --> 00:32:25,760
No extra charges.

458
00:32:28,920 --> 00:32:30,280
Darin had an issue with my dad,

459
00:32:30,920 --> 00:32:33,200
so I suspected she might have hurt him.

460
00:32:33,280 --> 00:32:34,520
And the conclusion?

461
00:32:35,120 --> 00:32:37,720
If something happens to Dad,
Darin loses more than she gains.

462
00:32:38,520 --> 00:32:40,440
So I believe she didn't do it.

463
00:32:44,440 --> 00:32:45,280
Sure.

464
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:56,480
What are you looking for?

465
00:32:57,080 --> 00:32:58,080
A mirror.

466
00:32:58,160 --> 00:32:59,960
I really want to hand you one right now.

467
00:33:00,040 --> 00:33:02,920
Because you look so, so jealous.

468
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:08,960
If you say jealous again,

469
00:33:09,040 --> 00:33:10,800
I'm going to charge 100 baht per time.

470
00:33:11,400 --> 00:33:13,200
Wow, jealous and stingy.

471
00:33:13,280 --> 00:33:14,880
- Stingy, stingy, sting--
- 100.

472
00:33:15,480 --> 00:33:16,560
Okay, just stingy. Not jealous.

473
00:33:17,800 --> 00:33:22,040
200. Plus water, milk, snacks, and…

474
00:33:22,120 --> 00:33:25,360
Oh, stingy, stingy, stingy.
Nothing else mixed in at all.

475
00:33:25,440 --> 00:33:26,360
400.

476
00:33:27,600 --> 00:33:28,840
- 400?
- Mm.

477
00:33:34,160 --> 00:33:36,360
Kanah said taking care of a patient

478
00:33:36,440 --> 00:33:39,720
takes physical and mental energy. Here.

479
00:33:41,800 --> 00:33:44,680
Eat a lot, okay? So you'll have
strength to take care of your dad.

480
00:33:48,040 --> 00:33:50,360
Mm… that sounds good.

481
00:33:50,440 --> 00:33:51,880
I take care of Dad,

482
00:33:52,600 --> 00:33:54,320
and you take care of me.

483
00:34:00,880 --> 00:34:03,960
Oh. Today, I ran into my dad.

484
00:34:04,040 --> 00:34:05,640
He came to visit your dad.

485
00:34:05,720 --> 00:34:08,000
Huh? How?

486
00:34:10,080 --> 00:34:12,159
I have the news covered up.

487
00:34:12,880 --> 00:34:15,000
Seems like Mrs. Mookmanee

488
00:34:15,080 --> 00:34:16,719
sent him to check on your dad.

489
00:34:16,800 --> 00:34:17,760
Mrs. Mookmanee?

490
00:34:30,600 --> 00:34:31,520
The news is about to start.

491
00:34:32,560 --> 00:34:35,040
Normally, you don't watch the news
while you exercise, Mom.

492
00:34:35,120 --> 00:34:37,000
The news about Mr. Tritot being in a coma.

493
00:34:37,600 --> 00:34:39,880
Uncle Tritot is in a coma?
What happened to him?

494
00:34:39,960 --> 00:34:41,320
Uh…

495
00:34:44,360 --> 00:34:46,080
Even Mika doesn't know yet.

496
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:48,600
He's the chairman of Be Rich.

497
00:34:48,679 --> 00:34:51,440
How can he get sick quietly like this?
Total loss of dignity.

498
00:34:52,800 --> 00:34:54,000
At Tritot's level,

499
00:34:54,080 --> 00:34:56,159
if he's dying,

500
00:34:56,239 --> 00:35:00,400
it has to make headlines.
It has to shake the whole stock market.

501
00:35:01,840 --> 00:35:04,800
You want his news
to make the stock price drop,

502
00:35:04,880 --> 00:35:06,200
so we can buy up shares, right?

503
00:35:07,840 --> 00:35:10,080
My daughter's getting smart now.

504
00:35:15,560 --> 00:35:16,400
Here it is.

505
00:35:17,760 --> 00:35:20,240
<i>After the protest incident</i>
<i>at a well-known leasing company</i>

506
00:35:20,320 --> 00:35:21,880
<i>that nearly turned into a tragedy,</i>

507
00:35:22,480 --> 00:35:26,120
<i>one of the executives came out</i>
<i>to negotiate with the protesters,</i>

508
00:35:26,200 --> 00:35:27,960
<i>and tensions were eased.</i>

509
00:35:28,040 --> 00:35:29,720
<i>If it weren't for Mr. Trai,</i>

510
00:35:29,800 --> 00:35:32,840
<i>I'd have killed myself.</i>
<i>Or I would've become a murderer.</i>

511
00:35:32,920 --> 00:35:35,280
Mr. Trai gave me a chance,

512
00:35:35,360 --> 00:35:38,680
let me go back to earning a living,
and helped with my debts.

513
00:35:39,280 --> 00:35:41,080
It's like he gave me a new life.

514
00:35:41,680 --> 00:35:43,040
<i>Thank you, Mr. Trai.</i>

515
00:35:43,640 --> 00:35:44,720
<i>Thank you very much.</i>

516
00:35:45,960 --> 00:35:48,640
<i>Our team interviewed many protesters.</i>

517
00:35:48,720 --> 00:35:50,480
<i>They all said the same thing.</i>

518
00:35:50,560 --> 00:35:54,040
<i>Be Rich under the leadership</i>
<i>of Trai Bowornmongkolphong</i>

519
00:35:54,120 --> 00:35:57,960
<i>isn't just lending money,</i>
<i>it's saving their lives as well.</i>

520
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:04,720
I told you to use the clip of Mika
having her meltdown to divert attention,

521
00:36:04,800 --> 00:36:09,000
in case Mrs. Mookmanee uses Dad being sick
to manipulate the stock price. Why me?

522
00:36:11,920 --> 00:36:12,800
Uh…

523
00:36:15,640 --> 00:36:17,320
I think this is better, Mr. Trai.

524
00:36:17,400 --> 00:36:19,400
Mr. Tritot has a lot of connections.

525
00:36:19,480 --> 00:36:21,680
We have to use them to our advantage.

526
00:36:21,760 --> 00:36:24,440
Even if Mrs. Mookmanee or anyone
leaks news about Mr. Tritot now,

527
00:36:24,520 --> 00:36:26,680
they can't discredit Be Rich anymore.

528
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:30,360
Look at you two,
working as a team, in perfect harmony.

529
00:36:30,440 --> 00:36:33,000
Did you even ask me
if I wanted to be the future of Be Rich?

530
00:36:34,640 --> 00:36:36,640
Oh? Where are you going?

531
00:36:36,720 --> 00:36:39,040
- I'm not telling you.
- Oh.

532
00:36:40,960 --> 00:36:42,240
- It's you.
- It's you.

533
00:36:44,040 --> 00:36:45,080
MRS. MOOKMANEE

534
00:36:48,440 --> 00:36:49,480
MRS. MOOKMANEE

535
00:36:52,440 --> 00:36:54,520
Aren't you going to pick up
Mrs. Mookmanee's call?

536
00:36:54,600 --> 00:36:56,960
She's probably calling
because she saw Trai's news.

537
00:36:57,760 --> 00:37:01,640
If Mrs. Mookmanee or her secretary
calls you, tell them I'm in a meeting.

538
00:37:02,360 --> 00:37:03,200
Yes, sir.

539
00:37:08,520 --> 00:37:11,440
So, is Mr. Trai really going
to be Be Rich's future?

540
00:37:20,160 --> 00:37:22,880
I'm heading out. I'm not coming back
to the office today.

541
00:37:35,360 --> 00:37:38,600
100% real herbal extract water.

542
00:37:38,680 --> 00:37:42,280
No sugar. Perfect for health lovers.

543
00:37:42,360 --> 00:37:46,200
Today only.
Buy two, get three bottles free!

544
00:37:46,280 --> 00:37:49,400
- Which one would you like to try?
- Here. Customer's here.

545
00:37:51,120 --> 00:37:52,800
You can taste it.

546
00:37:55,760 --> 00:37:56,920
You can taste it.

547
00:38:01,960 --> 00:38:02,880
Oh, hey.

548
00:38:06,440 --> 00:38:07,560
Oh?

549
00:38:08,360 --> 00:38:09,440
- It's good.
- Hey.

550
00:38:09,520 --> 00:38:12,400
Hey? That is your third one already.

551
00:38:12,480 --> 00:38:14,560
If you're going to drink this much,

552
00:38:14,640 --> 00:38:15,760
aren't you gonna buy one first?

553
00:38:18,080 --> 00:38:21,360
I'm not feeling great.
So I want to flush some waste out.

554
00:38:23,440 --> 00:38:26,480
But this detox
is for your intestines, you know.

555
00:38:28,640 --> 00:38:31,760
Someone like you needs a heart detox.

556
00:38:31,840 --> 00:38:33,040
That's why I came to you.

557
00:38:34,480 --> 00:38:36,040
So I'm a laxative now?

558
00:38:39,920 --> 00:38:40,760
Huh?

559
00:38:43,520 --> 00:38:45,080
Like this?

560
00:38:46,600 --> 00:38:48,840
- Pakbung.
- Watch out. Your saliva.

561
00:38:48,920 --> 00:38:49,920
- What?
- Cover for me.

562
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:51,200
Huh? What happened?

563
00:38:51,280 --> 00:38:54,600
This detox water hits so hard, seriously.

564
00:38:56,520 --> 00:38:57,960
- Samlee.
- I can't.

565
00:38:58,040 --> 00:39:00,000
Hey. Oh?

566
00:39:00,080 --> 00:39:02,680
- Whoa.
- Ooh, here it comes.

567
00:39:02,760 --> 00:39:05,960
If the boss comes and doesn't see you,
you're dead. Samlee!

568
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:10,280
You want to detox, right?

569
00:39:12,480 --> 00:39:13,560
I know a way.

570
00:39:14,880 --> 00:39:15,920
Work.

571
00:39:17,960 --> 00:39:19,640
That's my way of flushing out waste.

572
00:39:19,720 --> 00:39:21,920
Sweat it out.
It's better than crying it out.

573
00:39:22,000 --> 00:39:25,200
Once you're exhausted enough,
you'll forget everything.

574
00:39:28,800 --> 00:39:30,400
But I have a better way.

575
00:39:39,880 --> 00:39:40,840
Dad…

576
00:39:42,680 --> 00:39:43,800
Please come back soon.

577
00:39:45,760 --> 00:39:47,160
Be Rich is waiting for you.

578
00:39:49,120 --> 00:39:50,360
And so am I.

579
00:39:54,600 --> 00:39:56,560
Didn't you say you wanted
to eat fried chicken with me?

580
00:39:58,600 --> 00:40:00,320
I'm waiting, Dad.

581
00:40:04,200 --> 00:40:06,560
If you run off to eat with Mom,
just the two of you,

582
00:40:08,720 --> 00:40:09,920
I'd be really upset.

583
00:40:25,560 --> 00:40:26,760
Dad?

584
00:40:33,120 --> 00:40:35,560
Dad. Dad.

585
00:40:36,640 --> 00:40:37,480
Dad.

586
00:40:39,920 --> 00:40:42,840
- Please wait outside for now.
- Okay.

587
00:40:43,560 --> 00:40:44,640
Please.

588
00:40:56,360 --> 00:40:58,160
Tritot's condition is improving?

589
00:40:58,920 --> 00:41:00,200
Yes.

590
00:41:00,280 --> 00:41:02,600
I heard they've moved him
to a private VIP room now.

591
00:41:03,880 --> 00:41:05,600
Why doesn't he just die already?

592
00:41:12,200 --> 00:41:14,600
He's responding very well to treatment.

593
00:41:15,720 --> 00:41:17,200
No complications.

594
00:41:17,840 --> 00:41:20,240
Left-side and right-side
responses are normal.

595
00:41:20,840 --> 00:41:23,920
If he regains consciousness,
please let me know right away.

596
00:41:24,520 --> 00:41:26,560
Yes. Thank you so much.

597
00:41:27,440 --> 00:41:28,440
I'll take my leave.

598
00:41:41,680 --> 00:41:45,320
Thank you, Dad, for not leaving me.

599
00:42:04,960 --> 00:42:06,080
Dad?

600
00:42:07,160 --> 00:42:08,040
Dad.

601
00:42:10,040 --> 00:42:10,920
Dad…

602
00:42:12,600 --> 00:42:15,520
Push…

603
00:42:16,320 --> 00:42:18,240
- What? What did you say?
- Push…

604
00:42:19,360 --> 00:42:21,160
Watch out…

605
00:42:22,040 --> 00:42:23,560
- Watch out…
- What? What, Dad?

606
00:42:23,640 --> 00:42:24,520
Watch out…

607
00:42:26,160 --> 00:42:27,800
- Watch out…
- Watch out?

608
00:42:28,760 --> 00:42:30,440
Watch out?

609
00:42:30,520 --> 00:42:32,400
Dad, you know who did it?

610
00:42:35,080 --> 00:42:36,600
Was it Rachen?

611
00:42:42,160 --> 00:42:43,280
Was it Darin?

612
00:42:50,240 --> 00:42:52,160
Son…

613
00:42:52,240 --> 00:42:53,080
What?

614
00:42:54,840 --> 00:42:56,480
Mom…

615
00:42:57,920 --> 00:42:59,640
Mom?

616
00:42:59,720 --> 00:43:01,160
Did you say "Mom"?

617
00:43:09,120 --> 00:43:10,160
Dad…

618
00:43:45,920 --> 00:43:46,960
Mom?

619
00:43:48,520 --> 00:43:49,480
What does Mom have to do with this?

620
00:43:59,200 --> 00:44:00,080
Mr. Trai.

621
00:44:05,320 --> 00:44:08,920
I know you don't want me
to visit Mr. Tritot.

622
00:44:09,600 --> 00:44:10,720
But I'm worried.

623
00:44:11,400 --> 00:44:14,000
I don't want to just
sit at home and wait for news.

624
00:44:16,960 --> 00:44:18,840
Come sit first. Dad just fell asleep.

625
00:44:21,000 --> 00:44:23,680
You can wait here too,
in case he wakes up again.

626
00:44:29,280 --> 00:44:30,240
Thank you, Trai.

627
00:44:33,600 --> 00:44:37,640
I brought porridge too,
in case you get hungry.

628
00:44:41,760 --> 00:44:45,320
But if you don't want it, it's okay.

629
00:44:45,400 --> 00:44:46,720
I can take it back.

630
00:44:47,440 --> 00:44:49,880
It's fine. I haven't eaten anything.

631
00:44:55,680 --> 00:44:57,320
I didn't change the recipe at all.

632
00:44:57,400 --> 00:44:59,280
I used sea bass that you like.

633
00:45:09,080 --> 00:45:10,120
And there's a dipping sauce too.

634
00:45:18,880 --> 00:45:20,120
- Ah.
- Oh.

635
00:45:21,360 --> 00:45:22,760
It's all over your hands, Trai.

636
00:45:26,120 --> 00:45:27,680
You're so clumsy.

637
00:45:38,400 --> 00:45:39,440
Mr. Trai.

638
00:45:47,280 --> 00:45:48,080
Pakbung?

639
00:46:01,480 --> 00:46:03,280
I told you we shouldn't let them in yet.

640
00:46:04,240 --> 00:46:06,960
Then what do we tell Mr. Rachen
and Pakbung? "You can't go in."

641
00:46:07,040 --> 00:46:09,240
"Mr. Trai and Ms. Darin are talking."
Like that?

642
00:46:10,560 --> 00:46:13,360
It's bad either way. Two trains crashing.

643
00:46:14,200 --> 00:46:15,200
Every man for himself.

644
00:46:16,960 --> 00:46:18,240
What trains?

645
00:46:32,840 --> 00:46:35,360
You blocked me from visiting Dad,

646
00:46:35,440 --> 00:46:37,760
but you let Darin come near him?

647
00:46:40,400 --> 00:46:41,800
I didn't get to visit him either.

648
00:46:41,880 --> 00:46:45,200
- He just fell asleep. Trai doesn't want--
- Shut up. I'm not talking to you.

649
00:46:45,280 --> 00:46:47,280
If you're going to make a scene, go home.

650
00:46:47,360 --> 00:46:48,480
Dad needs to rest.

651
00:46:48,560 --> 00:46:50,160
Why, Trai?

652
00:46:50,240 --> 00:46:52,600
Why are you always
taking this woman's side?

653
00:46:52,680 --> 00:46:54,280
I'm not taking anyone's side.

654
00:46:54,360 --> 00:46:56,360
And I don't want trouble
with anyone either.

655
00:46:56,440 --> 00:46:57,520
Then look at what you're doing.

656
00:46:57,600 --> 00:46:59,000
This room isn't soundproof, Bro.

657
00:46:59,080 --> 00:47:02,120
Even if Dad's asleep, he can hear.
I don't want him to be stressed.

658
00:47:02,720 --> 00:47:04,520
If you can't control your emotions,

659
00:47:04,600 --> 00:47:06,560
go home now. I'm begging you.

660
00:47:07,840 --> 00:47:08,800
Mr. Trai.

661
00:47:10,680 --> 00:47:13,720
Can't you let Mr. Rachen go in
to see Mr. Tritot too?

662
00:47:19,280 --> 00:47:22,880
Trai just said
he wants Mr. Tritot to rest.

663
00:47:24,840 --> 00:47:26,440
Just a quiet visit.

664
00:47:26,520 --> 00:47:29,800
Standing by the bed, no talking.

665
00:47:29,880 --> 00:47:31,600
It won't bother him.

666
00:47:31,680 --> 00:47:34,360
Mr. Rachen is worried
about Mr. Tritot too.

667
00:47:44,000 --> 00:47:46,440
- How much did he pay you?
- Huh?

668
00:47:47,040 --> 00:47:48,680
Pakbung didn't take any money from me.

669
00:47:49,720 --> 00:47:51,040
So it's your choice.

670
00:47:52,400 --> 00:47:53,320
It's what you want to do.

671
00:47:55,000 --> 00:47:58,000
Don't get involved, Pakbung.
This isn't your business.

672
00:48:19,040 --> 00:48:20,280
I know, Dad.

673
00:48:20,880 --> 00:48:22,880
I know Rachen is worried about you.

674
00:48:23,680 --> 00:48:28,360
Since I'm not suspecting him anymore,
I should let him visit.

675
00:48:29,120 --> 00:48:30,520
But I don't like it, Dad.

676
00:48:31,120 --> 00:48:33,520
I don't like Rachen being with Pakbung.

677
00:48:33,600 --> 00:48:37,000
And I don't like Pakbung taking
Rachen's side either. I don't like it.

678
00:48:40,240 --> 00:48:41,120
Wait.

679
00:48:44,040 --> 00:48:46,680
Dad, am I being selfish again?

680
00:48:49,200 --> 00:48:51,760
Ugh. What the hell did you just say, Trai?

681
00:48:58,560 --> 00:48:59,840
I'll be right back, Dad.

682
00:49:05,200 --> 00:49:06,640
Trai, where are you going?

683
00:49:09,240 --> 00:49:11,000
Hey, Lee, Prarop.

684
00:49:13,200 --> 00:49:14,640
Lee, take Da home.

685
00:49:14,720 --> 00:49:16,920
- Yes, sir.
- Prarop, take care of Dad for me.

686
00:49:17,000 --> 00:49:17,960
Yes, sir.

687
00:49:25,520 --> 00:49:26,360
Did they leave already?

688
00:49:32,880 --> 00:49:35,920
PAKBUNG

689
00:49:44,480 --> 00:49:45,440
What the hell?

690
00:49:49,680 --> 00:49:50,960
My phone.

691
00:50:14,680 --> 00:50:16,000
MR. TRAI

692
00:50:16,080 --> 00:50:17,080
<i>Help.</i>

693
00:50:18,400 --> 00:50:19,400
Mr. Trai?

694
00:50:27,480 --> 00:50:29,240
Why did you hang up?

695
00:50:38,480 --> 00:50:39,640
Hey! Stop!

696
00:50:40,280 --> 00:50:41,640
Hey!

697
00:50:45,640 --> 00:50:46,480
Who are you?!

698
00:51:00,440 --> 00:51:01,560
Pakbung.

699
00:51:01,640 --> 00:51:03,400
Wait here.

700
00:51:03,480 --> 00:51:05,440
I'm going up to settle things with Trai.

701
00:51:05,520 --> 00:51:07,720
Today, I'm going
to visit Dad no matter what.

702
00:51:08,560 --> 00:51:09,600
Then I'm coming with you.

703
00:51:43,520 --> 00:51:46,120
Who are you? What do you want?

704
00:51:46,200 --> 00:51:48,080
I'm asking! What do you want?!

705
00:51:51,960 --> 00:51:54,040
Answer me. Answer me!

706
00:51:54,120 --> 00:51:55,720
Because of your dad's company.

707
00:51:55,800 --> 00:51:57,800
It put my dad in debt.

708
00:51:57,880 --> 00:51:59,680
My dad killed himself
because of you people!

709
00:52:00,560 --> 00:52:02,360
Trai, I'm going to kill you!

710
00:52:03,640 --> 00:52:05,880
It's not you. Who sent you?

711
00:52:05,960 --> 00:52:07,800
I'm asking, who sent you?

712
00:52:07,880 --> 00:52:10,800
I'm going to kill you!
You and your dad must die!

713
00:52:14,080 --> 00:52:15,160
Dad!

714
00:53:27,640 --> 00:53:28,480
Dad.

715
00:53:28,560 --> 00:53:30,680
Dad! Dad!

716
00:53:34,960 --> 00:53:37,280
Dad! Dad!

717
00:53:37,880 --> 00:53:38,760
Dad!

718
00:53:40,120 --> 00:53:42,520
What's wrong with Dad? Trai, what's wrong?

719
00:53:47,800 --> 00:53:50,960
Doctor! Nurse!

720
00:53:51,760 --> 00:53:53,960
Please wait outside.

721
00:53:55,720 --> 00:53:57,880
Cardiac arrest.
Prepare emergency equipment

722
00:53:57,960 --> 00:54:00,840
and the defib.
Please call the on-duty doctor.

723
00:54:01,560 --> 00:54:04,400
Excuse me, please step back.
Please wait outside.

724
00:54:04,480 --> 00:54:07,440
Please wait outside. Please.

725
00:55:15,960 --> 00:55:17,240
This is because of you, Trai.

726
00:55:17,320 --> 00:55:19,120
You suspected me.

727
00:55:19,200 --> 00:55:20,720
You blocked me.

728
00:55:20,800 --> 00:55:22,720
You acted like you loved Dad so much.

729
00:55:22,800 --> 00:55:24,400
Look what you did to him!

730
00:55:24,480 --> 00:55:26,600
How could you let this happen?!

731
00:55:26,680 --> 00:55:29,760
How could you let Dad die?!

732
00:55:31,400 --> 00:55:33,480
Huh?!

733
00:55:33,560 --> 00:55:35,280
Answer me!

734
00:55:37,480 --> 00:55:39,160
I couldn't protect Dad…

735
00:55:39,760 --> 00:55:42,720
You couldn't protect him,
so why the hell did you stop me?!

736
00:55:42,800 --> 00:55:45,160
Why did you stop me?! Huh?!

737
00:55:45,240 --> 00:55:46,680
Why did you stop me?!

738
00:55:46,760 --> 00:55:48,360
Please stop, Mr. Rachen.

739
00:55:48,440 --> 00:55:52,000
Come here! Open your eyes and look!

740
00:55:52,080 --> 00:55:54,040
Burn this into your skull.

741
00:55:54,120 --> 00:55:56,000
Dad died because of you.

742
00:55:56,080 --> 00:55:58,080
Because of a shitty son like you!

743
00:55:58,760 --> 00:56:01,000
Since you were born,
what have you ever done for Dad?

744
00:56:01,760 --> 00:56:04,440
You never did a damn thing for him.

745
00:56:06,680 --> 00:56:08,160
Then why?

746
00:56:08,760 --> 00:56:10,600
Why did you get to be with him?

747
00:56:10,680 --> 00:56:14,680
Why were you the one
with him to the very end?

748
00:56:16,640 --> 00:56:18,760
Why were you his son?

749
00:56:18,840 --> 00:56:21,160
Why were you the one Dad loved most?

750
00:56:21,240 --> 00:56:23,920
Answer me! Why?!

751
00:56:24,000 --> 00:56:26,240
- Damn it!
- I'm sorry.

752
00:56:44,440 --> 00:56:45,480
Mr. Rachen.

753
00:56:56,440 --> 00:56:57,280
Pakbung.

754
00:56:58,520 --> 00:56:59,400
Can you help?

755
00:57:03,440 --> 00:57:05,120
I'm sorry…

756
00:57:30,160 --> 00:57:33,120
I'm sorry, Dad. I'm sorry…

757
00:57:34,080 --> 00:57:36,200
You died because of me. I'm sorry.

758
00:58:09,360 --> 00:58:12,720
You're the true reason Dad died.
Remember that!

759
00:58:12,800 --> 00:58:16,400
Without Dad's light,
without Mom's starlight,

760
00:58:17,520 --> 00:58:19,160
I have no one.

761
00:58:19,240 --> 00:58:20,600
<i>He's just a friend</i>

762
00:58:20,680 --> 00:58:22,400
<i>who doesn't even care about me.</i>

763
00:58:22,480 --> 00:58:24,600
Why am I this emotional?

764
00:58:24,680 --> 00:58:27,240
Because you're already more than friends.

765
00:58:27,320 --> 00:58:28,920
Dad gave all the shares to me?

766
00:58:29,520 --> 00:58:32,800
Yes. All the Be Rich shares
under Mr. Tritot's name

767
00:58:32,880 --> 00:58:34,880
were intended
to be given to you, Mr. Trai.

768
00:58:34,960 --> 00:58:36,800
And this house as well.

769
00:58:36,880 --> 00:58:39,480
You get everything without even trying.

770
00:58:39,560 --> 00:58:41,880
<i>In the end, look what happens.</i>
<i>Dad still didn't choose me.</i>

771
00:58:42,840 --> 00:58:45,160
I really want to know.
When Dad sat in this chair,

772
00:58:45,240 --> 00:58:46,880
who did he make so angry?

773
00:58:46,960 --> 00:58:49,760
<i>I'm going to talk about appointing</i>
<i>the new Be Rich chairman.</i>

774
00:58:49,840 --> 00:58:52,760
Trai shouldn't get anything
from Dad, especially that position.

775
00:58:52,840 --> 00:58:55,240
I, Trai Bowornmongkolphong,

776
00:58:55,320 --> 00:58:59,280
would like to declare my candidacy
to be chairman of Be Rich.

777
00:59:46,680 --> 00:59:49,280
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
